      p Siena is a gloriously beautiful medieval town built upon three hills in the heart of scenic Tuscany.
        It is a city full of churches, museums, and great views over the surrounding countryside. 
        In the centre of the town you will find Piazza del Campo. Stepping into this spectacular shell-shaped piazza is simply memorizing, it's like a film set. It is famous for the Palio, which is a horse race run here twice a year, in the summer time. These races pit the 17 different neighborhoods of Siena against each other. You can’t go anywhere in Siena without hearing about the Palio, it is what unites but at the same time divides the Sienese more than anything else.

