    h2.text-center The Cathedral
    p Another sight for the eyes is the mesmerising Siena Cathedral. The facade of the cathedral is incredibly intricate and full of detail. The whole cathedral was painted, sculpted, and decorated by the most celebrated Italian artists of that time. It is just amazing and I’m afraid these words and photos just don’t give it justice.
    The interior is absolutely jaw dropping, yet another marvel in itself. It is like a museum, with its black and white marble pillars, marble floor panels, beautiful renaissances frescos, a huge bronze dome, a sculpture of St. Peter by Michelangelo. It definetly gives the cathedral a luxurious feel, with no expense spared in displaying the historical wealth of Siena.

